TEHRAN , April 10 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- The Iranian government today demanded the Turkish government recall its four diplomats who were accused of espionage .
Iran 's official news agency IRNA reported that Iran 's Foreign Ministry asked Turkey to terminate the mission of four Turkish diplomats in Iran and recall them to Ankara .
A spokesman from the ministry was quoted as saying `` such a decision was taken as a result of the failure of the Turkish diplomats to observe the diplomatic norms in Iran . ''
The report said that several espionage networks led by some Turkish diplomats have recently been discovered in Tehran , Tabriz and Orumiyeh .
Iran announced here Tuesday night that it has smashed a Turkish espionage ring mostly made up of Turkish diplomats in the Islamic Republic .
However , the intelligence director general of East Azarbaijan province did not say exactly how many were arrested .
The intelligence director general provided their identifications of the four linked to the espionage ring as follows : Ardal Kuzoghlu , Turkish political attache at the Consulate in Orumiyeh ; Khalil Olomoz , political attache at the Turkish Embassy in Tehran ; Ali Hussein Hakan Kadakal , political attache at the Orumiyeh Consulate ; and Qadri Jan , political attache at the consulate in Tabriz .
He said further information on the espionage ring will be put at the disposal of the media and the public opinion in coming days .
The intelligence officer was quoted as saying that confessions of those arrested and the documents discovered from the spy den indicate that the spies garnered information and put it at the disposal of the Turkish Intelligence Agency .
The official said that members of the ring conspired against the Islamic Republic of Iran and intended to interfere in Iran 's internal affairs .
They were trying to form clandestine groups in an effort to carry out unlawful operations and acts of sabotage against the sovereignty of the Islamic Republic of Iran .
The report said that the confessions of the members of the espionage ring indicate that a number of Turkish intelligence officers who were planted under the guise of diplomats at the Turkish Embassy in Tehran and its consulates in Tabriz and Orumiyeh , spearheaded these covert activities .
Observers here noted that the latest move taken by the Iranian government would jeopardize the deteriorating relations between Iran and Turkey .
Relations between Iran and Turkey have turned ice-cold after the publications of news report that Turkey and Israel signed a military agreement under which the Israeli air force is permitted to train in Turkish skies .
In a meeting with visiting Turkish Deputy Foreign Minister AliToygun , Iran 's First Vice - President Hassan Habibi said , `` If the news is correct , it is going to hurt the feeling of the Islamic nation . ''
In reply , Toygun said that Ankara attached great importance to its friendly relations with other countries .
It would not allow any country to disrupt its friendly relations with Iran .
According to an Iranian report , the Turkish official denied that his country had put its airspace and base at the disposal of Israel .
